The paper is about the 2019 DAVIS Challenge on Video Object Segmentation, which is a task related to computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The challenge also involves the use of unsupervised learning, which suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the challenge involves video processing, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
